 Hostinger VPS Deployment Plan for Gema Platform

 Overview

 Deploy both frontend (React/Vite) and backend (Node.js/Express + BullMQ worker) to single Hostinger VPS with:
 - OS: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS
 - Web Server: Nginx (reverse proxy + static files + SSL)
 - Process Manager: PM2 (API server + worker process)
 - Databases: MongoDB Atlas + Redis Cloud (managed)
 - SSL: Let's Encrypt (free)

 ---
 Phase 1: VPS Initial Setup

 1.1 Server Security Hardening

 # Connect as root
 ssh root@your-hostinger-vps-ip

 # System updates
 apt update && apt upgrade -y

 # Create app user
 adduser gemaapp
 usermod -aG sudo gemaapp

 # SSH key auth (copy from root to gemaapp)
 mkdir -p /home/gemaapp/.ssh
 cp ~/.ssh/authorized_keys /home/gemaapp/.ssh/
 chown -R gemaapp:gemaapp /home/gemaapp/.ssh
 chmod 700 /home/gemaapp/.ssh
 chmod 600 /home/gemaapp/.ssh/authorized_keys

 # Harden SSH (/etc/ssh/sshd_config)
 # Set: PermitRootLogin no, PasswordAuthentication no
 systemctl restart sshd

 # Firewall (UFW)
 ufw allow 22/tcp && ufw allow 80/tcp && ufw allow 443/tcp
 ufw enable

 # Brute force protection
 apt install fail2ban -y

 1.2 Install Required Software

 su - gemaapp

 # Node.js 20.x
 curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | sudo -E bash -
 sudo apt install -y nodejs build-essential

 # PM2, Nginx, Git, Certbot
 sudo npm install -g pm2
 sudo apt install nginx git certbot python3-certbot-nginx -y

