 Phase 2: Backend Deployment

 2.1 Directory Structure

 sudo mkdir -p /var/www/gema /var/log/gema
 sudo chown -R gemaapp:gemaapp /var/www/gema /var/log/gema

 cd /var/www/gema
 git clone <your-repo-url> .
 cd backend
 npm install
 npm run build

 2.2 Environment Configuration

 Critical file: E:\coding\gema\backend\.env

 Required services setup BEFORE deployment:
 1. MongoDB Atlas: Create cluster, whitelist IPs, get connection string
 2. Redis Cloud: Create database, SET EVICTION POLICY TO noeviction (CRITICAL for BullMQ)
 3. Firebase: Generate service account private key
 4. Cloudinary: Get cloud name + API credentials
 5. Stripe: Get live API keys
 6. Email: Configure SMTP (Hostinger SMTP or Gmail App Password)

 Key variables:
 - MONGODB_URI - Atlas connection string
 - REDIS_HOST, REDIS_PORT, REDIS_PASSWORD - Redis Cloud credentials
 - JWT_SECRET / JWT_REFRESH_SECRET - Generate 64-char random strings
 - FRONTEND_URL=https://yourdomain.com - For CORS
 - FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY - Escape newlines as \n

 2.3 PM2 Configuration

 Update file: E:\coding\gema\backend\ecosystem.config.js

 Change paths:
 - cwd: '/var/www/gema/backend'
 - Log paths: /var/log/gema/api-*.log, /var/log/gema/worker-*.log
 - Set instances: 1 for VPS (adjust if multi-core)
 - max_memory_restart: '800M' (adjust based on RAM)

 Start processes:
 cd /var/www/gema/backend
 pm2 start ecosystem.config.js --env production
 pm2 save
 pm2 startup systemd  # Run output command
 pm2 install pm2-logrotate

 2.4 Redis Cloud Configuration

 CRITICAL: Verify eviction policy:
 redis-cli -h <host> -p <port> -a <password> CONFIG GET maxmemory-policy
 # Must return: "noeviction"

 If not set, configure in Redis Cloud dashboard:
 - Configuration → Advanced → Eviction Policy → noeviction

 See: E:\coding\gema\backend\REDIS_CONFIG.md

