 Phase 3: Frontend Deployment

 3.1 Build Frontend

 cd /var/www/gema/frontend

 # Update API URL in .env.production
 # VITE_API_URL=https://yourdomain.com/api

 npm install
 npm run build

 # Deploy to Nginx directory
 sudo mkdir -p /var/www/gema/frontend-dist
 sudo cp -r dist/* /var/www/gema/frontend-dist/
 sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www/gema/frontend-dist

 Key file: E:\coding\gema\frontend\vite.config.ts - Build config with chunk splitting

 ---
 Phase 4: Nginx Configuration

 4.1 Create Nginx Config

 File: /etc/nginx/sites-available/gema

 Key features:
 - HTTP → HTTPS redirect
 - Backend proxy: /api/* → http://127.0.0.1:5000
 - Frontend: Static files from /var/www/gema/frontend-dist
 - Rate limiting: 100 req/min general, 10 req/min auth, 20 req/min analytics
 - Security headers (HSTS, X-Frame-Options, CSP, etc.)
 - Gzip compression
 - Asset caching (1 year for js/css, no cache for HTML/sw.js)

 # Enable site
 sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/gema /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
 sudo rm /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default

 # Test and restart
 sudo nginx -t
 sudo systemctl restart nginx

 4.2 SSL/TLS Setup

 sudo systemctl stop nginx
 sudo certbot certonly --standalone -d yourdomain.com -d www.yourdomain.com
 sudo systemctl start nginx

 # Enable auto-renewal
 sudo systemctl enable certbot.timer

