 Troubleshooting Quick Reference

 Backend won't start:
 - Check logs: pm2 logs gema-api --err --lines 50
 - Verify MongoDB URI in .env
 - Check Redis connection (noeviction policy set?)
 - Ensure port 5000 not in use: sudo netstat -tulpn | grep 5000

 Worker not processing jobs:
 - Check logs: pm2 logs gema-worker --lines 100
 - Verify Redis eviction policy: Must be noeviction
 - Test Redis connection: redis-cli -h <host> -p <port> -a <pass> PING

 Nginx 502 Bad Gateway:
 - Backend running? pm2 status
 - Test backend directly: curl http://localhost:5000/api/health
 - Check Nginx logs: sudo tail -f /var/log/nginx/error.log

 Frontend not loading:
 - Files exist? ls /var/www/gema/frontend-dist/
 - Nginx logs: sudo tail -f /var/log/nginx/error.log
 - Browser console for CORS errors (check FRONTEND_URL in backend .env)

 CORS errors:
 - Verify FRONTEND_URL in backend .env
 - Restart backend: pm2 restart gema-api
 - Check headers: curl -I -H "Origin: https://yourdomain.com" https://yourdomain.com/api/health

